Subject: Re: Filler Virus (PC)

lin@ug.cs.dal.ca (David Lin) writes:

> We have a mild problem here. Scan v97b detected the [Filler] virus with
> the command line:
> 	scan c: /chkhi
> The program instructed us to power down and then reboot with a floppy.
> We did this but then we could not detect the virus again. This of course
> meant that Clean failed.

Sigh... It's in the FAQ and I am really tired of answering this
question... You are using CPAV or TNTVIRUS. Their resident part keeps
its scan strings in memory unencrypted. This is what SCAN finds. When
you boot from a floppy, the resident scanner CPAV is not present, so
SCAN finds nothing. Read the docs for CPAV, it plainly says that it is
incompatible with any other anti-virus software.

> Does anyone out there know how we can get rid of the [Filler] virus? 

In this particular case you should just get rid of CPAV...

